## Gate D Objectives
<!-- Gate D is the Build Quality Gate. It confirms that delivery is functionally complete to sufficient quality to enter formal validation (Phase 5). All critical defects must be resolved, integration must be stable, and AI/ML model evaluation must meet targets. -->

Gate D validates:
- All committed features are built and meet acceptance criteria
- No open Critical defects; High defects have accepted remediation plans
- Integration is stable across all integration points
- AI/ML model evaluation meets performance thresholds
- Code quality metrics meet agreed targets
- Security scan completed with no critical findings

